This paper is likely to belong to the cs.AI sub-category as it deals with the development of an automated testing tool for detecting erroneous behaviors of DNN-driven autonomous cars. It also involves the use of Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) which is a common topic in the cs.AI sub-category. 

The paper also involves the use of sensors like camera and LiDAR, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) research. 

Additionally, the paper involves the systematic exploration of different parts of the DNN logic, which is a common topic in the cs.LG sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves the design and implementation of a software tool, which falls under the cs.SE sub-category.
